                <head>110. Circular telegram 170 to certain American Republic posts, July 26<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d110fn1">U.S. plan to recognize Ecuadorean junta
                        by July 31 if several other Hemisphere countries do so by then.
                        Confidential. 1 p. Kennedy Library, National Security Files, Countries
                        Series, Ecuador, July to November, 1963.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1963-07-26T16:29:00">July 26, 1963, 4:29
                            p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d110-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d110-1"/>
                <p>On assumption several other Hemisphere countries recognize Ecuadorean junta by
                    July 30–31 U.S. Government planning extend recognition July 31. You are
                    requested informally consult host govern<pb facs="0449" n="274" type="typeset"
                        xml:id="pg_274"/>ment <gloss target="#t_re_1">re</gloss> above timing and
                    any developments their plans on recognition. Action posts other than BA,
                    Santiago and Rio may also say U.S. understands Argentina, Chile and Brazil
                    considering recognition by July 31.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_RD_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD_1">Rusk</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
